## Route Constants

Never hardcode path strings. Always use `ROUTES` from `@/config/routes`:

```js
// src/config/routes.js
export const ROUTES = {
  HOME: "/",
  ABOUT: "/about",
  PRODUCTS: "/products",
  PRODUCT_DETAIL: (slug) => `/products/${slug}`,
  SERVICES: "/services",
  SERVICES_CONSULTANTS: "/services/consultants",
  SERVICES_MAINTENANCE: "/services/maintenance",
  SERVICES_INSPECTIONS: "/services/inspections",
  INDUSTRIES_DIST_GRID: "/industries/distribution-grid",
  SOLUTIONS_SOFTWARE: "/solutions/software-application",
  CONTACT: "/contact",
};
```

Usage:

```jsx
import Link from 'next/link'
import { ROUTES } from '@/config/routes'

<Link href={ROUTES.ABOUT}>About Us</Link>
<Link href={ROUTES.PRODUCT_DETAIL(product.slug)}>View Product</Link>
```

---

## `app/` Is Routing Only

The `app/` directory contains ONLY:

- `page.jsx` files вЂ” compose feature components, fetch data, export metadata
- `layout.jsx` files вЂ” shell wrappers
- `loading.jsx`, `error.jsx`, `not-found.jsx` вЂ” special Next.js files
- `route.js` вЂ” API handlers

**Never define a reusable component inside `app/`.** Move it to `components/` or `features/`.
